# 1) Legacy /330 short-URL alias for the $330 audit offer — 308 to canonical /micro-offer.
#    /330 → /micro-offer → /micro-offer/ (two hops: this redirect + CF Pages auto trailing-slash).
#    Both `/330` and `/330/` paths are covered so any external / short-URL link lands on canonical.
#    CF Pages uses :splat on the destination side to substitute the wildcard segment.
/330            /micro-offer            308
/330/           /micro-offer/           308
/330/*          /micro-offer/:splat     308

# 1b) Self-contained owner login — bypasses the SPA bundle and the service worker
#     so a stale SW or browser extension can't break the auth flow.
/owner-login         /owner-login.html        301

# 1c) Catch-all proxy /v1/* → /api/v1-proxy/* so the SPA bundle can talk
#     same-origin to admin APIs and avoid cross-origin blocks. The Pages Function
#     at functions/api/v1-proxy/[[path]].js forwards to the real Worker.
/v1/*               /api/v1-proxy/:splat      200
/owner-login         /owner-login.html        301

# 2) Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback: preserve clean direct routes for Wouter client routing.
/*    /index.html   200